Thanks ---------------------- Forwarded by Hunter S Shively/HOU/ECT on 01/09/2001 10:08 AM --------------------------- From: Demetrion Ware@ENRON on 01/04/2001 10:47 AM To: Hunter S Shively/HOU/ECT@ECT, Patrice L Mims/HOU/ECT@ECT, Robert Superty/HOU/ECT@ECT, Colin Tonks/HOU/ECT@ECT cc: Subject: Peoples Energy Project Status The Peoples Energy Project is Currently On the Public Internet. The version that has been released is not in its final phase. Many of the rules of the business have to be tested and changed to reflect the correct data representation. The only way for us to do this is to have the current users who will be using the system to verify the correctness of the data. Due to this fact, it is not recommended that this system be used for trading purposes until the portion of the system being worked on is verified to be in fact correct in its representation of the data. It is still imperitive that this system is viewed daily for its correctness, validation, fault tolerance and efficiency on a daily basis, for this is where we devise our metrics on the systems completeness. Currently there is a new update version of the application that resides in Chicago that delivers the data to the website. Our current contact has been sent to a training in Canada and will not be available until Jan 20, 2001. Due to this I would like to set up a meeting to: Application Status Report 1. Please advise if you are unable to attend. Topics for discussion are: - Discuss limitation of pipelines/paths to be initially provided on EOL. Judy-
